==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precipitancy
<hw>Pre*cip"i*tan*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Precipitant</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
precipitant, or precipitate; headlong hurry; excessive or rash haste in
resolving, forming an opinion, or executing a purpose; precipitation;
<as>as, the <ex>precipitancy</ex> of youth</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Precipitance</xex> of judgment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precipitant</ent>⟦br⟧
